\begin_layout Paragraph*
Theoretical Model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

, firms are endowed with initial asset-in-place (AIP) and with stochastic
 initial earning 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{t}^{0}$
\end_inset

.
 It could decide to make an IC investment 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 with success rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

.
 Firms have productive capacity 
\begin_inset Formula $K=K(X)$
\end_inset

 which depends on IC investment.
 Fixed cost is 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{K}K(X)$
\end_inset

 and variable cost is normalized to zero.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\emph on
incremental 
\emph default
earning from new IC investment is: 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{t}^{n}=P_{t}(X,\Gamma_{t},K(X))-f_{k}K(X)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{t}$
\end_inset

 is random sale productivity; 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{t}$
\end_inset

 is revenue function, and can be rewritten as 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{t}=\Gamma_{t}X^{a}\sqrt{K(X)}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $0<a<1$
\end_inset

 is marginal revenue product of IC investment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The stochastic pricing kernel 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{t+1}=m_{t}exp(-r-\frac{\sigma_{v}^{2}}{2}-v_{t+1})$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 is risk-free rate, and 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

 is shocks.
 The intrinsic systematic risk of new investment 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=cov(\epsilon,v)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Conditional on 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

, 
\series bold
\emph on
pre-exercise firm valuation
\series default
\emph default
 is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V_{t}=V_{t}^{A}-V_{t}^{X}+V_{t}^{N}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}^{A}$
\end_inset

 is value of initial asset-in-place, 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}^{X}$
\end_inset

 is discounted fixed cost associated with IC investment, and 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}^{N}$
\end_inset

 is value of potential innovation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Post-exercise firm valuation is: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V_{t}=V_{t}^{A}+V_{t}^{P}-V_{t}^{F}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}^{A}$
\end_inset

 is value of initial asset-in-place, 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}^{P}$
\end_inset

 is discounted value of new revenue part, and 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}^{F}$
\end_inset

 is fixed operating cost of both 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, they can write the expected return as a value-weighted average of
 component assets' expected returns.
 Specifically, in pre- and post-arrival/exercise regimes, we have:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
E_{t}[R_{t+1}]=\begin{cases}
\begin{array}{cc}
\bar{\omega}_{t}^{A}e^{r+\theta}-\bar{\omega}_{t}^{X}e^{r}+\bar{\omega}_{t}^{N}\bar{R}^{N} & if\, t<T\\
(\hat{\omega}_{t}^{A}+\hat{\omega}_{t}^{P})e^{r+\theta}-\hat{\omega}_{t}^{F}R^{r} & if\, t>T
\end{array}\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega^{j}=\frac{V^{j}}{V_{t}}$
\end_inset

 is weight of component asset 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

, so 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\omega}^{X}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\omega}^{F}$
\end_inset

 reflect operating leverage; 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{r+\theta}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{r}$
\end_inset

 are risky asset return and risk-free return; 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{R}^{N}=e^{r+\theta}-(e^{\theta}-1)(1-\lambda)$
\end_inset

 is return on potential innovation, will be converted to revenue with risky
 asset return (but depend on success rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

), so 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{r}<\bar{R}^{N}<e^{r+\theta}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The impact of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 on future expected returns is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial E_{t}[R_{t+1}]}{\partial X}=\begin{cases}
\begin{array}{cc}
\frac{\partial\bar{\omega}_{t}^{A}}{\partial X}(e^{r+\theta}-e^{r})+\frac{\partial\bar{\omega}_{t}^{N}}{\partial X}(\bar{R}^{N}-e^{r})+\bar{\omega}_{t}^{N}\lambda'(X)(e^{\theta}-1) & if\, t<T\\
\frac{\partial\hat{\omega}_{t}^{F}}{\partial X}(e^{r+\theta}-e^{r}) & if\, t>T
\end{array}\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph*
Intuitions:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When t>T (after innovations are generated and exercised): 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\hat{\omega}_{t}^{F}}{\partial X}>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial E_{t}[R_{t+1}]}{\partial X}>0$
\end_inset

